paragraphs.title: Show Customers who are Predicted to Buy Insurance.
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT A.*, B.* FROM N1_APPLY_RESULT A, N1_TEST_DATA B WHERE PREDICTION = ${PREDICTION='Yes','Yes'|'No'} and a.customer_id = b.customer_id;

paragraphs.title: Interactive Pie Chart of "Likely Buyers"
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT A.*, B.* FROM N1_APPLY_RESULT A, N1_TEST_DATA B WHERE PREDICTION = ${PREDICTION='Yes','Yes'|'No'} and a.customer_id = b.customer_id;

%sql
SELECT * from(
SELECT CUSTOMER_ID, PREDICTION_PROBABILITY(N1_CLASS_MODEL, 'Yes'  USING A.*) prob
 FROM N1_APPLY_RESULT A)
 WHERE prob > 0.2;
paragraphs.title: Select Customers Above a Stated Threshold Probability of Buying Insurance

paragraphs.text:
%sql
Select prediction_probability(N1_CLASS_MODEL, 'Yes'
  USING 7800 as bank_funds, 125 as checking_amount, 20 ascredit_balance, 55 as age, 'Married' as marital_status, 250 as MONEY_MONTLY_OVERDRAWN, 1 as house_ownership)
from dual;
